Note:
Unit tests for compiler/frontend/import_system/crypto/ecdsa.runa.

Test vectors come from RFC 6979 Appendix A.2.5 (ECDSA, P-256, SHA-256,
deterministic k) and from algorithmic self-consistency:

  Private key x = C9AFA9D845BA75166B5C215767B1D6934E50C3DB36E89B127B8A622B120F6721
  Public Ux = 60FED4BA255A9D31C961EB74C6356D68C049B8923B61FA6CE669622E60F29FB6
  Public Uy = 7903FE1008B8BC99A41AE9E95628BC64F2F1B20C2D7E9F5177A3C294D4462299

  Vector "sample":
    expected k = A6E3C57DD01ABE90086538398355DD4C3B17AA873382B0F24D6129493D8AAD60
    expected r = EFD48B2AACB6A8FD1140DD9CD45E81D69D2C877B56AAF991C34D0EA84EAF3716
    expected s = F7CB1C942D657C41D436C7A1B6E29F65F3E900DBB9AFF4064DC4AB2F843ACDA8

  Vector "test":
    expected r = F1ABB023518351CD71D881567B1EA663ED3EFCF6C5132B354F28D3B0B7D38367
    expected s = 019F4113742A2B14BD25926B49C649155F267E60D3814B4C0CC84250E46F0083

The tests construct the private key, run sign(), and compare r/s against
the RFC 6979 expected values byte-for-byte via constant-time compare.
Then a self-verify confirms the signature accepts. Then DER round-trip
is exercised.
:End Note

Import "tests/test_utils.runa" as T
Import "runtime/core/memory/arena.runa" as Arena
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/memory_core.runa" as Memory
Import "compiler/frontend/import_system/crypto/bigint.runa" as BigInt
Import "compiler/frontend/import_system/crypto/curve_p256.runa" as P256
Import "compiler/frontend/import_system/crypto/ecdsa.runa" as ECDSA

Note: Write a 32-byte big-endian hex blob into a Memory buffer.
Note: Each hex pair is provided as a separate byte argument so the buffer
Note: lookup walks fixed memory locations.
